The paper deals with communication over channels with sparse impulse responses, which is a topic in information theory and communication theory (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The use of pilot-aided orthogonal frequency-division multiplexing (OFDM) is also mentioned, which is a common technique in wireless communication (cs.SI, cs.NI). Finally, the paper considers the effect of noise on the communication system, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SP).
